feed.subtitle: Area incorporating the Neds Corner property (Trust for Nature) and the adjoining Murray River frontage.

entry.title: Hemiptera spp., Medicago minima
entry.content: Tiny yellow Hemipteran-like insect on Medicago minima. Less than 1.5mm long.

entry.title: Lycosidae spp.

entry.title: Aglaosoma variegata
entry.content: Large, hairy caterpillar found feeding on Cattle Bush (Alectryon oleifolius subsp. canescens). Size similar to adult pointer finger, both in length and girth. Thanks to Cathy Powers and Peter Marriott for identification.

entry.title: Nacaduba biocellata biocellata
